=================================================  
 
The Atkinson People is a trip to the more recent past, when Rowan Atkinson was just starting out in comedy. 

First broadcast on Radio 3 in 1978, this series of satirical investigations into the lives of - fictional - great men was written by Atkinson and Richard Curtis and produced by Griff Rhys Jones. 

These 4 shows each profiled a fictional famous person, as played by Atkinson, interacting with other characters played by Hugh Thomas and Peter Wilson.
